<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Meet great black scientists
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ ``African American Healers'' by Clinton Cox (John
Wiley &AMP; Sons, $22.95) offers profiles of 25 African-Americans who
made a difference in science and medicine. It highlights, among
others, Susie King Taylor, a Civil War nurse, and Charles Drew,
father of the blood bank. We wish there were more photographs and
that some of the pictures weren't so grainy (but hey, they're old).
Check this one out if you do a book report for Black History Month.
_ Julie Bookman
</P>
