 &HT;    But officer, I only dabbed it behind my ears
 &HT;    By Gregory Kallenberg
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ It's a flashlight! It's a breath analyzer! It's
annoying! It's the cops' newest weapon, the P.A.S. III! The P.A.S.
III, otherwise known as ``the sniffer,'' is a flashlight that
registers alcohol on the breath of whomever the light is pointed
at. It also can detect if anyone in a car has been drinking. It's
not annoying for what it does. We totally condone getting all the
drunks off the road. The P.A.S. III irks because it already has a
strong track record of false positives. Police in Richardson,
Texas, have reported positive results from people with mouthwash on
their breath and from people wearing strong cologne or perfume.
While the Austin Police Department won't confirm or deny it is
