<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ It's business as usual this morning at the
local cafe. My retired farmer buddies are talking politics over
their first cup of decaf. As is also usual, nobody's agreeing on
anything other than they'd all sooner vote for Tiny Hodelman than
for Al Gore or ``Little George.'' ``If the rest of Ohio feels the
way you guys do,'' I warn them, ``the upcoming primary is going to
knock the pollsters for a loop...and who's Tiny Hodelman?''
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA, Fla. _ I would like to say a few words in
favor of Post-Valentine's Day. Today is a day dedicated to life
after old valentines. It celebrates ex- girlfriends, old
boyfriends, first wives, high school sweethearts, rebound
relationships and special friends who really did want to be
friends, after all. (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
