   &UR; WHAT A DIFFERENCE A YEAR MAKES FOR BRAZIL'S PRESIDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In the darkest hours of the past year, Brazilian President
Fernando Henrique Cardoso seemed to cling to the hope that by
grimly sticking to an unpopular austerity program, not only would
his country's economy return to growth but his own popularity and
authority would eventually recover from the disorderly devaluation
of January 1999. &QL;
</P>
