 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HAVE FACTORY, WILL TRAVEL: THE NEW `VIRTUAL' FACTORIES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   At first glance, the electronics factory near Guadalajara looks
like any other. But look more closely and you might notice
something odd. One of the lines churns out Web TV set-top boxes,
which connect television to the Net, for Philips, a Dutch
consumer-electronics giant. The line next to it makes the same
device for Sony, Philips's arch-rival.
</P>
<P>
   It is part of a trend sweeping electronics: factories for hire. &QL;
</P>
