</P>
<P>
   The second thing is to start campaigning like a challenger, as
he did in the 1994 governor's race, when he fought a popular
incumbent for every vote.
</P>
<P>
   But the most urgent change goes even deeper. He needs to tear up
the script and throw away the cue cards.
</P>
<P>
   Bush is much brighter than his frat-boy act leads one to
suppose. He should mingle with the press. Bush is also a likeable
fellow. He should cut down on the pre-programmed dirges from the
platform and reach out to his audience.
</P>
<P>
   An old badge from the glory days of the 1980s reads ``Let Reagan
be Reagan.'' The Bush campaign's best chance of surviving lies in
letting W. be W. &QL; 
