<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; JESSE VENTURA JUMPS SHIP; CAN REFORM PARTY STAY AFLOAT? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The unpredictable governor of Minnesota, Jesse Ventura,
announced Friday that he is taking his state's Reform Party out of
the national organization to protest against the infighting that
has plagued it in recent months. The problem for the Reform Party
now, though, is not just the fallout from the rivalry between its
two big personalities, Ventura and founder Ross Perot. While they
squabbled, the party's platform has been hijacked by challengers
John McCain and Bill Bradley. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Mary Dejevsky, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (425 words) &QL;
