<P>
   &UR; BOOK FINDS `CIVILIZED' LONDON `GOING THE WAY OF THE DODO' &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Assuming you manage to get out of Heathrow Airport (``chaotic
and overcrowded'') in one piece, the next hazard for the unwary
tourist arriving in London is White Van Man, who is just waiting to
``punch your lights out,'' before you are ripped off at a hotel
which, wherever it is, ``is going to take a great wad out of your
pocket.'' So says the new pull-no-punches edition of the ``Lonely
Planet: London'' travel guide. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Kate Watson-Smyth &QL;
