   The pickers emerge from their houses, walking through the long
grass surrounding the rose plantation, just as dawn gives way to
the first rays of sunlight at 6 a.m. They earn slightly more than
the minimum wage, but with housing and water provided by the farm.
</P>
<P>
   With unemployment at record levels in Zimbabwe, most people are
just grateful for a job.
