<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`MUSE' BRILLIANT BROOKS; `WINSLOW BOY' TOP MAMET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Muse'' (DVD) _ Albert Brooks can't seem to
catch a break. Perhaps his sense of irony and humiliation will
never cross over into the mainstream, but his loyal fans can enjoy,
again, his brilliant, comic assessment of Hollywood. The cameos by
Rob Reiner and Martin Scorsese are excellent, and Jeff Bridges is
perfectly cast as a tennis-playing screenwriter who can't get the
ball over the net but his self-image is so secure, he doesn't care.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Winslow Boy'' (DVD) _ This might be David Mamet's best
movie. His adaptation of Terence Rattigan's 1946 play based on a
1910 legal case is convincingly compact. Mamet's understated style
perfectly suits the Victorian-era story of a young boy on trial for
stealing a five-shilling postal order. Rebecca Pidgeon superbly
underplays her role as a feminist, and Nigel Hawthorne is terrific
as the family patriarch. Cinematographer Benoit Delhomme's imagery
is perfectly married to the visual style of the period. Ariculate,
smart, suspenseful, and artfully unpretentious.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: While some of us are champing at the bit for the DVD
release of such classics as ``Lawrence of Arabia'' and ``The
Treasure of the Sierra Madre,'' new releases are generating the
profits. According to Video Business magazine, the top-selling
theatrical DVDs of 1999 were, in ascending order: ``Wild Wild
West,'' ``Rush Hour,'' ``Blade,'' ``Big Daddy,'' ``Enemy of the
State,'' ``Titanic,'' ``Armageddon,'' ``Austin Powers: The Spy Who
Shagged Me,'' ``Saving Private Ryan,'' and, at No. 1, ``The
Matrix.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Tuesday:``Grey Wolf,'' ``Breakfast of
Champions,'' ``Mob Queen,'' ``Big Fella'' (DVD), ``Song of
Freedom'' (DVD), ``In Too Deep,'' ``Daughters of the Dust'' (DVD),
``Total Recall 2070,'' ``Entropy,'' ``Joe the King'' (DVD), ``The
Lovers on the Bridge.'' Feb. 22: ``Get Bruce!,'' ``Bats,'' ``Tail
Lights Fade'' (DVD), ``Galaxina,'' ``Conspirators of Pleasure''
(DVD). Feb. 29: ``Stigmata'' (DVD), ``Random Hearts'' (DVD), ``The
Suburbans'' (DVD), ``One Man's Hero'' (DVD). March 7: ``Eyes Wide
Shut'' (DVD), ``The Mirror'' (DVD), ``King of Masks'' (DVD),
``Crime and Punishment.'' March 14: ``Outside Providence,''
``Guinevere,'' ``The Love Bug,'' ``Bandits'' (DVD), ``The Prophecy
3.'' March 21: ``Jakob the Liar'' (American version; on DVD),
``Endurance,'' ``Horror Express'' (DVD), ``Velocity Trap'' (DVD),
``Swing.'' March 28: ``Voices From a Locked Room.'' April 4: ``Star
Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
