<P>
   BUSH-McCAIN (Saluda, S.C.) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush and Sen.
John McCain, R-Ariz., are running neck-and-neck as they begin their
final week of campaigning before this state's Saturday primary.
Both candidates are seeking the support of Democrats and
independents, who are eligible to take part in the Republican
primary. By DAN FREEDMAN and STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The unseemly fight George Bush and
John McCain in South Carolina is a battle of images rather than
issues. But they are both so frantic that their efforts to distort
each other's identity are often downright silly. McCain is not a
loony liberal, as Bush contended, and Bush is not Bill Clinton, as
McCain claimed. McCain was wise to pull away from such madness.
Bush ought to do the same. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
