<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-14 14:24 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6457 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r l BC-LOIS-CONVENTION-HNS &LR;      02-14 0440
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LOIS-CONVENTION-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     LOIS IS VERY POPULAR AT THIS CONVENTION 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By IHOSVANI RODRIGUES  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ Alyssa is popular. So are Jacob, Maria, Joshua,
Austin, Hunter, Antonio, Hannah, Jared, Mackenzie, Marisa, Dakota,
Alejandro, Zach, Jose, Ashley, Madison and Cristina.
</P>
<P>
   Lois, however, is a different story.
</P>
<P>
   Unlike the names above, Lois failed to make the Social Security
Administration's top 100 names for births in 1999. Lois never came
close, not even in the top 385.
</P>
<P>
   The last time the name Lois made it onto any list of popular
baby names was in the 1930s, when it ranked an admirable 18th.
Ethel, Margaret and Harold also were on that list.
</P>
<P>
   Through Wednesday, San Antonio may have the largest
concentration of women named Lois in the world. About 150 people
named Lois _ each a proud member of the National Lois Club _ are
expected to attend the group's annual convention here.
</P>
<P>
   As in most years, Lois conventioneers will have no real order of
business or itinerary except hanging out with others bearing the
same name. There is not even a profound reason why they chose San
Antonio. (There are no local chapters or members in the entire
state of Texas.)
</P>
<P>
   ``I have a daughter in San Antonio, so I thought we should go
down there and visit,'' said Lois Rightor, a convention organizer
from Columbus, Ohio. ``I heard it's really pretty down there.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's always a traditional joke for someone to walk into our
meeting room and yell out `Phone call for Lois,''' Rightor said.
</P>
<P>
   The group of Loises has met biennially since 1979, once going as
far as Ireland. What is different about the San Antonio convention
is that it will be the first time the group has met two years
consecutively.
</P>
<P>
   The name of Lois is a dying name, they explain.
</P>
<P>
   ``We planned a cruise last year, but by the time we planned it
and actually had it, three members had died,'' Rightor said.
``We've since decided we'll have the convention every year instead
of every two years.''
</P>
<P>
   To help promote the name and everything Lois, there is a Lois
Club in 20 U.S. states, Canada, Norway, Australia, the United
Kingdom and New Zealand. There is a competing organization, the
Lois Link, mostly active in Canada and California.
</P>
<P>
   The upper Midwest is huge Lois country. The biggest clubs are in
Minnesota and Wisconsin. The Milwaukee club has more than 300
members, including a man named Lois _ the only known male in a Lois
Club.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (For information on the Lois organization, call Lois Rightor at
614-868-0327.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-14-00 1424EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
