<P>
   HKN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of the Times column on
hockey. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-LEWIS (Atlanta) _ Bond hearing is held for Ray Lewis,
accused in two stabbing deaths. By Jon Nordheimer.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-THOMAS-TRIBUTE (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Kansas City pays tribute
to Derrick Thomas at an all-day viewing in his favorite end zone in
Arrowhead Stadium. By Thomas George.
</P>
<P>
   DOG-SHOW (New York) _ The first day of the Dog Show. By Richard
Sandomir.
</P>
<P>
   SKATE-TV-RATINGS (Undated) _ In the first weekend since
September without pro football, the highest rated televised event
was the U.S. National Figure Skating Championships. Michelle Kwan's
victory in the women's competition Saturday night helped ABC to an
8.5 overnight Nielsen rating, up 23 percent from last year. The
pairs competition, which was shown during the first hour, rated a
7.6. By Richard Sandomir.
</P>
