   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-McCAIN (Saluda, S.C.) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush and Sen.
John McCain of Arizona are running neck-and-neck in South Carolina
as they begin their final week of campaigning before Saturday's
Republican primary. Both candidates spar over McCain's views on gun
control and public financing of elections. By DAN FREEDMAN and
STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BORDER-BOUNTY (Harlingen, Texas) _ An internal Border Patrol
memo says a Mexican drug cartel is offering $200,000 to anyone who
kills a U.S. law enforcement agent. By JAMES PINKERTON.
</P>
<P>
   NASA-EROS (Houston) _ After a near-flawless rocket firing, a
robot craft becomes the first spacecraft to orbit an asteroid,
settling into a Valentine's Day rendezvous with a space rock named
for the Greek god of love. The Near Earth Asteroid Rendezvous
spacecraft will spend a year in orbit of Eros and will gather
information that one day may help humans defend the Earth against a
``killer asteroid'' like the one thought to have wiped out the
dinosaurs. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   GODS-CAMPUS (Nacogdoches, Texas) _ Deep in the heart of the
Bible Belt, a religious confrontation has pitted East Texas pagans
against Christians over a religious banner that hangs at Stephen F.
Austin State University. By JOHN WILLIAMS.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   US-DRUGS (Washington) _ U.S. intelligence and law-enforcement
agencies pledge to improve cooperation in fighting the illegal
narcotics trade, conceding that federal teamwork in the war on
drugs has been sorely lacking. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ROCKETS _ As the Houston Rockets enter the second half of
this season of false starts, they maintain they can still make a
serious run at an NBA playoff berth. But realistically, the best
this team can hope for is a strong finish that could set the stage
for future success. By JONATHAN FEIGEN.
</P>
<P>
   With: BKN-BLINEBURY-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BBN-NL-WEST (Undated) _ Preview of the National League West,
where the retooled Los Angeles Dodgers and San Diego Padres will
try to unseat the Arizona Diamondbacks. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The unseemly fight between George
Bush and John McCain in South Carolina is a battle of images rather
than issues. But they are both so frantic that their efforts to
distort each other's identity are often downright silly. McCain is
not a loony liberal, as Bush contended, and Bush is not Bill
Clinton, as McCain claimed. McCain was wise to pull away from such
madness. Bush ought to do the same. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   ROBISON-COLUMN (Austin, Texas) _ Money in politics may be evil,
as John McCain has constantly tried to hammer home, but it is also
the lifeblood of a presidential campaign, as he very well knows.
And no amount of rhetoric on the campaign stump has been able to
dislodge this inherent conflict. By CLAY ROBISON.
</P>
