Monday grew out of a line of thunderstorms that swept across the
South during the night and by morning extended all along the East
Coast. Thunderstorms also ripped off roofs and knocked down trees
in parts of Alabama, and earlier strong wind destroyed at least six
houses in Arkansas and injured two people. Trees and power lines
also were down in parts of Mississippi and Tennessee, where one
woman was injured by wind-blown debris. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
