   HEALTHEON _ Healtheon/WebMD Corp. has signed definitive
agreements to acquire Medical Manager Corporation, a leading
provider of physician practice management systems, and its publicly
traded subsidiary, CareInsite, Inc., a provider of innovative
healthcare network and clinical communication services. (Kanell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-ACCESS _ CEO Jack Phillips continues his romp toward
becoming a major player in international long-distance: World
Access makes two acquisition announcements, one for WorldxChange, a
$709 million deal for a company whose business is mostly overseas,
the other a $500 million purchase for Star Telecom (a letter of
intent for that one was already announced). Atlanta-based World
Access also closes a third deal, giving the ambitious, rapidly
growing company a run rate of nearly $3 billion. (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
