   &UR; ZIMBABWE'S THORNY RED ROSES FOR HORNY VALENTINE'S LOVERS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   As most of the millions who are sending and receiving roses for
Valentine's Day today know only too well, the path of true love is
a rough one. The rose growers of Zimbabwe, where many Valentine
roses began their journey, will tell you that the path from
tropical farm to British florist is not particularly smooth
either. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Alex Duval Smith, The Independent of London &QL;
