<P>
   &UR; MICROSOFT `BETS THE RANCH' ON $8 BILLION WINDOWS 2000 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It has been four years in the making, and cost Microsoft some $8
billion to produce. Now, Windows 2000, the software giant's latest
offering is ready to make its debut this Thursday, Feb. 17. But
will it sell? And more importantly, can Windows 2000 underpin the
company's future as its management hopes? That question, more than
the antitrust case against Microsoft, may determine the company's
future. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Marshall, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for Thursday, Feb. 17 launch of Windows 2000) &QL;
</P>
