<P>
   CAMPAIGN-GOP (Saluda, S.C.) _ Heading into one of the most
critical debates thus far in the Republican primary race, Governor
George W. Bush hints he will launch a new offensive on Senator John
S. McCain's past voting record; McCain excoriates Bush for
conducting a ``trash and garbage offensive.'' By Curtis Wilkie and
Anne E. Kornblut.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-DEMOCRATS (San Francisco) _ Al Gore's repetition of the
claim that Bill Bradley's health care plan will endanger many with
HIV, angers Bradley. He accuses Gore of dishonesty and hypocrisy.
By Bob Hohler.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FAA-TAILPLANE (Undated) _ Inspection of more than 1,000
jetliners with the same tail design as the Alaska Airlines MD-80
which crashed off California two weeks ago finds at least 23
airplanes had some problem with the mechanism which moves the
stabilizer. By Matthew Brelis. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   ESTROGEN-STUDY (Undated) _ National Cancer Institute study shows
that postmenopausal women who take progestin with estrogen may be
increasing their risk of breast cancer more than if they took
estrogen alone. By Judy Foreman. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   BIGDIG-COSTS (Boston) _ The management firm overseeing the Big
Dig can't promise the project can be completed for $12.2 billion,
setting off fears the price will soar higher. By Thomas Palmer.
1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   THEOLOGIANS-APPROVAL (Undated) _ Some Catholic theologians say
they expect to defy a new Catholic regulation requiring approval to
teach from their local bishop. By Michael Paulson. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   ARMED-RANGERS (Undated) _ Saying the northern woods have become
a more dangerous place, Maine's forest rangers are backing a bill
to allow them to carry guns. Officials say it puts the rangers'
Smokey-the-Bear image in jeopardy for nothing. By Ellen Barry. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; TV-LETTERMAN (Undated) _ Talk show host David Letterman,
recuperating from quintple bypass heart surgery, says he'll tape
his first return show Friday. By Don Aucoin. 800 words.
</P>
