   GA-STORMS-NYT (Camilla, Ga.) _ Tornadoes tore through a section
of southwest Georgia overnight, killing more than 20 people and
injuring at least 100, shearing off roofs, uprooting statuesque
pecan trees and snapping off pines like toothpicks. Gov. Roy Barnes
