but it is one of those odd twists of politics that he is trying to
do this by running against the controlled, high-gloss techniques
that Reagan brought to presidential campaigns. For McCain is still
brandishing as his main campaign weapon his relentless
accessibility. Much of this openness is a way to get free publicity
to counter the financial advantage of his main competitor, Gov.
George W. Bush. But more and more, McCain drops suggestions that
