<HEADLINE>
MAKING USE OF THE MILLENNIUM
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Rama Lama &LR; , a man who doesn't substitute a smiley face for a
dotted i in his signature _ for one thing, there's no ``i'' in his
name _ suggests that everyone make the goose eggs in 2000 ``into
little eyes.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's easy. Your readers should just get in the habit of
doodling in the little balls within sockets so thoughtfully
provided by our new millennium. Call me a cockeyed optimist, but I
think this could really turn things around.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. A Life magazine poll found that 49 percent of Americans
think the federal government is withholding information from them
about the existence of UFOs.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE IMPORTANCE OF BEING LEONARDO &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Leonardo DiCaprio &LR;  is on the cover of this week's Time
magazine, not, as cynics might think, because he's promoting his
new movie, ``The Beach.'' DiCaprio is an important international
figure, an  &UR; Al Gore &LR;  supporter and chairman of Earth Day 2000
(especially interesting in light of environmentalists' fury at the
re-sculpturing of the Thai landscape for ``The Beach'').
</P>
<P>
   In an interview with DiCaprio, Time's  &UR; Joel Stein &LR;  shares some
never-before-revealed information, including the fact that the film
star carries a discount card for Ralph's supermarket in his wallet
and actually shops for groceries.
</P>
<P>
   Stein is so amazed by that fact that he offers to take DiCaprio
to the market and pay for his groceries. Honoring the public's
right to know, the magazine reprints the receipt and grocery list
for the supermarket visit.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE SHOPPING NEWS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ David Elliott &LR;  thinks ads for sperm donors paying $45 an
offering and ads paying $10,000 an egg constitute a clear case of
gender discrimination.
</P>
<P>
   Careful perusal of the egg ad, in the Stanford Daily, reveals a
preference for ``proven college-level athletic ability''; the sperm
ad, in the Daily Cal, states a special need for Jewish men.
</P>
<P>
   So millions of  &UR; Albert Einstein &LR; s are less expensive than one
 &UR; Brandi Chastain &LR; ?
</P>
<P>
   _ If your electronic rodent is looking grungy, Elle magazine
points the way to a sterling silver mouse made by Asprey &AMP; Garrard
of England. The price is $1,350.
</P>
<P>
   _ Crystal earrings made by  &UR; Liz Palacios &LR;  Designs will be worn
by  &UR; Lorraine Bracco &LR;  on the last episode of this season's run of
``The Sopranos.'' Most shows don't credit the jewelry designer, but
the company sends word that its wares also have been worn on the
shows ``Ladies Man,'' and  &LR; ``Veronica's Closet,'' ``Melrose
Place,'' ``Beverly Hills, 90210,'' ``Caroline in the City,''
``Friends,'' ``ER'' and many others.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ A  &UR; Jesse Ventura &LR;  segment on ``The View'' Wednesday shows the
governor ice-fishing, shouting into the hole that a fish should
bite the hook, and sure enough, catching a fish. The governor
described this all on his radio show, broadcast last week. What he
failed to mention, though, was that the fish had been caught by a
local man before the taping began.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a very light, fluffy piece, not a news piece,'' said
 &UR; Karl Nilsson &LR; , publicist for ``The View.'' A spokesman for Ventura
said ABC producers are ``on their own.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Michael Medeiros &LR; , checking his Yellow Pages for stories told
by the headings, discovered Clergy-Closet.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Jerri Nielsen &LR; , the physician who had to be airlifted from
the South Pole after she diagnosed herself with breast cancer, has
sold a book to Talk Miramax Books about the experience.
Entertainment Weekly says the contract is in the high six figures
and includes a triple play: Talk Book, Talk magazine serial rights
and Miramax movie.
</P>
<P>
   The book is to be published next fall, a year after the Air
National Guard rescue operation that brought Nielsen home.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm married to an intensely beautiful woman who is on the
covers of those magazines. ... Look at the covers of most of the
magazines and all the actresses look like porno stars. They're all
dropping their clothes. I'm always proud of Uma that at least it's
just her face on the cover of Elle magazine. It isn't her ass or
her nipples. It's very strange. You never saw Meryl Streep doing
that. You never saw Jessica Lange doing that.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Ethan Hawke, who is married to Uma Thurman, in the Times of
London.
</P>
</TEXT>
