   Careful perusal of the egg ad, in the Stanford Daily, reveals a
preference for ``proven college-level athletic ability''; the sperm
ad, in the Daily Cal, states a special need for Jewish men.
</P>
<P>
   So millions of  &UR; Albert Einstein &LR; s are less expensive than one
 &UR; Brandi Chastain &LR; ?
</P>
<P>
   _ If your electronic rodent is looking grungy, Elle magazine
points the way to a sterling silver mouse made by Asprey &AMP; Garrard
of England. The price is $1,350.
</P>
<P>
   _ Crystal earrings made by  &UR; Liz Palacios &LR;  Designs will be worn
by  &UR; Lorraine Bracco &LR;  on the last episode of this season's run of
``The Sopranos.'' Most shows don't credit the jewelry designer, but
the company sends word that its wares also have been worn on the
shows ``Ladies Man,'' and  &LR; ``Veronica's Closet,'' ``Melrose
Place,'' ``Beverly Hills, 90210,'' ``Caroline in the City,''
``Friends,'' ``ER'' and many others.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ A  &UR; Jesse Ventura &LR;  segment on ``The View'' Wednesday shows the
governor ice-fishing, shouting into the hole that a fish should
bite the hook, and sure enough, catching a fish. The governor
described this all on his radio show, broadcast last week. What he
failed to mention, though, was that the fish had been caught by a
local man before the taping began.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a very light, fluffy piece, not a news piece,'' said
 &UR; Karl Nilsson &LR; , publicist for ``The View.'' A spokesman for Ventura
said ABC producers are ``on their own.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Michael Medeiros &LR; , checking his Yellow Pages for stories told
by the headings, discovered Clergy-Closet.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Jerri Nielsen &LR; , the physician who had to be airlifted from
the South Pole after she diagnosed herself with breast cancer, has
sold a book to Talk Miramax Books about the experience.
Entertainment Weekly says the contract is in the high six figures
and includes a triple play: Talk Book, Talk magazine serial rights
and Miramax movie.
</P>
<P>
   The book is to be published next fall, a year after the Air
National Guard rescue operation that brought Nielsen home.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
