<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-14 20:27 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6887 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     02-14 0789
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
By LEAH GARCHIK 
Copyright 2000 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; MAKE-A-WILL WEEK STARTS TODAY &QL;  &LR; 
Nonprofit groups hoping to be remembered kindly are sponsoring 26
workshops this week in the Bay Area for Make-a-Will Week. Some
famous examples of the genre:
</P>
<P>
   - &UR; Ben Franklin  &LR; left $4,000 in 1790, with instructions that it
go to the state of Philadelphia in 200 years. By that time, it was
worth more than $2 million.
</P>
<P>
   - &UR; Malcolm Forbes  &LR; left money to 30 motorcycle clubs.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; -Vladimir Horowitz &LR;  left money for students at Juilliard, but
specified that no competitions be conducted in his name.
</P>
<P>
   - &UR; Harry Houdini &LR;  left money to the Society of American
Musicians.
</P>
<P>
   P.S. The American Veterinary Medical Association and the
American Veterinary Dental Society have declared February
``National Pet Dental Health Month.''
</P>
<P>
   P.P.S. Close readers may notice that although Personals is not a
sentiment-free zone, Personals is (except for this mention) a
Valentine's Day-free zone. Buy your sweetie a candy bar when your
sweetie is not expecting it.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NORVILLE DOES TIME &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Deborah Norville &LR; , distinguished member of the ``Inside
Edition'' team, entered a jail in North Carolina over the weekend
to spend five days there and report on the experience.
</P>
<P>
   ``The best way to portray what life behind bars is really like
is to spend a considerable amount of time behind bars,'' announced
Norville last week. ``One day wouldn't do it.''
</P>
<P>
   She said she was nervous about the assignment. ``I'm probably
going in with the same trepidation that any lady in there probably
feels.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - With Austrian politics in mind, Rep. &UR; Connie Morella &LR; , R-Md.,
announced she would boycott the National Chamber Orchestra's
``Night in Old Vienna,'' upon which music director  &UR; Piotr Gajewski &LR; 
canceled the event. Morella, co-chair of the event, told the
Washington Post that she was sorry for the orchestra and would
``definitely help with subsequent fund-raisers.''
</P>
