INHERITING-1 (Undated) - For the third time in a century, America's
leaders are facing vital questions about the nation's role in the
world. During World War I, it was, ``Should America abandon
Arcadian isolation and enter the world stage?'' After World War II,
it was, ``What strategy can be devised for containing Communism?''
Now, policymakers are debating a third and equally momentous
question: ``Should the world's only superpower govern the planet?''
