<TEXT>
<P>
   The 1stLd-Writethru on GA-STORMS is now scheduled to move by
9:40 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   GA-STORMS (Camilla, Ga.) _ Attacking under cover of darkness and
with little warning, a streak of tornadoes rumbled through
southwest Georgia early Monday morning, killing at least 22 people,
injuring more than 100 and transforming peaceful subdivisions into
wastelands of debris. Because the storms began just before
midnight, many sleeping residents had no idea they were at risk
until they heard the cracking of pine trees and the shattering of
window panes. Some did not even have time to get out of bed and
into a closet.
</P>
<P>
   By Kevin Sack.
</P>
<P>
   1,300 words.
</P>
<P>
   With photos NYT8-13 and map.
</P>
<P>
   The N.Y. Times News Service.
</P>
