services Monday. About 3,000 ethnic Albanians turned out for
Hajradine's funeral who mourners said was killed Sunday by French
troops. The ethnically divided city of Mitrovica appeared calm
Monday, a day after fighting erupted between French soldiers and
snipers. (Andrew Testa/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) MITROVICE, Yugoslavia -- Feb. 14, 2000 --
KOSOVO-MITROVICA -- French troops search ethnic Albanians near a
street Monday where several French soldiers were wounded during
unrest Sunday. Attacks by ethnic Albanians on the peacekeepers sent
to Kosovo to protect them could undermine support for the
peacekeeping mission, NATO's chief said Monday. (Andrew Testa/The
New York Times)
</P>
